(108, 1, 'Section 1 - Presentation', '', 43, '<!-- Section 1 -->\r\n<section class=\"g-py-100\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center g-mb-50--md g-mb-0--md\">\r\n<div class=\"u-heading-v2-3--bottom g-brd-primary g-mb-30\">\r\n<h2 class=\"h1 u-heading-v2__title g-color-gray-dark-v2 text-uppercase g-font-weight-700\">Go Faster</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"g-font-size-18 g-line-height-2 g-mb-30\">\r\n<p>The purpose of this cms is to offer a fast way to build web sites such public web sites, blogs or extranet.</p>\r\n<p>Anit cms provides an all in one tool kit to create your web site or web application faster.<br /> It provides native features as an extranet management, a blog template, a files management or security features.<br /> It allows to keep focused on the contents and the way to present it.<br /> You can also develop your own modules or implement third-party modules provided by the zend community. It is also easy to add your own php classes in the project</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<!--<a class=\"btn u-btn-primary u-shadow-v21 g-font-size-12 text-uppercase g-font-weight-600 g-rounded-50 g-py-15 g-px-25 g-mr-15 g-mb-10 g-mb-0--sm\" href=\"#\"> Buy Full Version </a> <small class=\"d-block d-sm-inline-block g-color-gray-dark-v5 g-font-size-12\">*Exclusive item on Wrapboostrap Marketpalce</small></div>-->\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center text-center g-overflow-hidden\"><img class=\"img-fluid w-75\" src=\"../../assets/img/inline/inline11.png\" alt=\"Image Description\" data-animation=\"fadeInUp\" data-animation-delay=\"0\" data-animation-duration=\"1000\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!-- End Section 1 -->', NULL, NULL, 'content', '', '', '2019-01-14 08:04:58', '', '', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(109, 1, 'Section 2 - Concept', '', 44, '<!-- Section 2 -->\r\n<section class=\"g-bg-purple g-color-white g-py-100\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center text-center g-overflow-hidden g-mb-50--md g-mb-0--md\"><img class=\"img-fluid w-75\" src=\"../../assets/img/inline/inline11.png\" alt=\"Image Description\" data-animation=\"fadeInUp\" data-animation-delay=\"0\" data-animation-duration=\"1000\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center\">\r\n<div class=\"u-heading-v2-3--bottom g-brd-white g-mb-30\">\r\n<h2 class=\"h1 u-heading-v2__title text-uppercase g-font-weight-700\">Concept</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"g-font-size-18 g-line-height-2 g-mb-30\">\r\n<p>The main concept is that your web page is made from blocks.<br /> You think and design your web page as ordered blocks. You declare your web page and its blocks in the cms.<br /> The goal is just to be focused on the design of your web page with the different blocks provided by the application.</p>\r\n<p>The first level is your web page.<br /> Inside your web page you have section blocks.<br /> And finally inside your section blocks you have content blocks.<br /> You have many types of content block to fullfill your different needs.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<!--<a class=\"btn u-shadow-v21 g-bg-white-opacity-0_2 g-color-white g-brd-white--hover g-color-purple--hover g-bg-white--hover g-font-size-12 text-uppercase g-font-weight-600 g-rounded-50 g-py-15 g-px-25 g-mr-15 g-mb-10 g-mb-0--sm\" href=\"#\"> Buy Full Version </a> \r\n<small class=\"d-block d-sm-inline-block g-color-white-opacity-0_8 g-font-size-12\">*Exclusive item on Wrapboostrap Marketpalce</small>--></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!-- End Section 2 -->', NULL, NULL, 'content', '', '', '2019-01-14 17:52:08', '', '', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(110, 1, 'Section 3 - Blocks', '', 45, '<!-- Section 4 -->\r\n<section class=\"g-py-100\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center g-mb-50--md g-mb-0--md\">\r\n<div class=\"u-heading-v2-3--bottom g-brd-primary g-mb-30\">\r\n<h2 class=\"h1 u-heading-v2__title g-color-gray-dark-v2 text-uppercase g-font-weight-700\">Blocks</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"g-font-size-18 g-line-height-2 g-mb-30\">\r\n<p>You have many types of content block:<br /> - standard: html content that you can edit with an editor + title and a subtitle<br /> - gallery: standard content and with additional images fields<br /> - blog: gallery content with additional fields like author, date...<br /> - map: standard content with GPS coordinates and its related information details<br /> - links: it allows to use an existing content in another section. You can use the content as is or you can customize it.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center text-center g-overflow-hidden\"><img class=\"img-fluid w-75\" src=\"../../assets/img/inline/inline11.png\" alt=\"Image Description\" data-animation=\"fadeInUp\" data-animation-delay=\"0\" data-animation-duration=\"1000\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!-- End Section 4 -->', NULL, NULL, 'content', '', '', '2019-01-15 17:55:40', '', '', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(111, 1, 'Section 4 - Files management', '', 46, '<!-- Section 6 -->\r\n<section class=\"g-bg-pink g-color-white g-py-100\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center text-center g-overflow-hidden g-mb-50 g-mb-0--md\"><img class=\"img-fluid w-75\" src=\"../../assets/img/inline/inline11.png\" alt=\"Image Description\" data-animation=\"fadeInUp\" data-animation-delay=\"0\" data-animation-duration=\"1000\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center\">\r\n<div class=\"u-heading-v2-3--bottom g-brd-white g-mb-30\">\r\n<h2 class=\"h1 u-heading-v2__title text-uppercase g-font-weight-700\">Files Management</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"g-font-size-18 g-line-height-2 g-mb-30\">\r\n<h5>Back-office</h5>\r\n<p>Anit cms provides a file management. You can upload a lot of types of files. When you create or update a content block you have the ability to add a link of a file. A table below the form is displayed to show all the files uploaded. You can copy and paste the relative url and add it in the appropriate content block property.</p>\r\n<h5>Extranet</h5>\r\n<p>You have the ability to allow an extranet\'s user to upload a file. It is an useful feature. For example, your client need to communicate a document to one your department. You can validate, invalidate or delete the file provided by the users in the back-office. For an image, you can rotate it and save it in order to have the right position.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>\r\n<!-- End Section 6 -->', NULL, NULL, 'content', '', '', '2019-01-17 07:32:49', '', '', '', 0, 0, NULL),
(113, 1, 'Section 6 - Forms', '', 48, '<section class=\"g-py-100\">\r\n<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"row\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center g-mb-50--md g-mb-0--md\">\r\n<div class=\"u-heading-v2-3--bottom g-brd-primary g-mb-30\">\r\n<h2 class=\"h1 u-heading-v2__title g-color-gray-dark-v2 text-uppercase g-font-weight-700\">Forms</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"g-font-size-18 g-line-height-2 g-mb-30\">\r\n<p>You have forms provided by the cms:<br /> - Contact form<br /> - Comment form (usually for blog)<br /> - Registration form (to be registered to an extranet)<br /> - Forgotten password form (extranet)<br /> - New Password form (extranet)<br /> - User information update form (extranet)</p>\r\n<p>You will find basic examples in the cms to implement these elements in your web site.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-6 align-self-center text-center g-overflow-hidden\"><img class=\"img-fluid w-75\" src=\"../../assets/img/inline/inline11.png\" alt=\"Image Description\" data-animation=\"fadeInUp\" data-animation-delay=\"0\" data-animation-duration=\"1000\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section>', NULL, NULL, 'content', '', '', '2019-01-18 18:43:48', '', '', '', 0, 0, NULL),
